Detailed Description

Definition of the format of a data type

A Format is the definition of the format for a data structure, currently only XDR like format is supported. MPI like format will be supported as a compilation of XDR like format.

Constructor & Destructor Documentation

Util::Format::Format ( Id  fmid,
size_t  sz,
const std::string &  name 
)

cstor with parameter to define a format. The caller should give an unique identifier for the type, as it could be return by kaapi_get_swid() macro.

Parameters:
fmid an unique system wide identifier
sz the size of the object class the format represents
name the name of the format
See also:
kaapi_get_swid
